A vintage-style illustration of a single copper telephone wire stretching across a vast desert landscape at dusk, with data represented as tiny glowing particles moving sluggishly along the wire like sand through an hourglass. On one end, a small cozy house with warm window light sits patiently, while the other end disappears into distant mountains. The sky transitions from burnt orange to deep purple, with a crescent moon rising. The particles bunch up and crawl forward in fits and starts, visualizing the frustrating asymmetry of upload versus download speeds. Muted earth tones with pops of amber and electric blue for the data particles.
